article.description: — Jake DiMichele had 15 points in Duquesne's 68-59 win against Fordham on Saturday.
article.headline: DiMichele scores 15 as Duquesne beats Fordham 68-59
article.linkText: DiMichele scores 15 as Duquesne beats Fordham 68-59
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — Jake DiMichele had 15 points in Duquesne's 68-59 win against Fordham on Saturday. DiMichele shot 6 for 10 (0 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free throw line for the Dukes (11-8, 2-5 Atlantic 10 Conference). David Dixon scored 12 points while going 5 of 7 and 2 of 3 from the free throw line, and added six rebounds, three steals, and three blocks. Jimmy Clark III shot 3 for 10 (0 for 3 from 3-point range) and 6 of 10 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points, while adding seven assists. Elijah Gray led the way for the Rams (9-11, 3-4) with 19 points, eight rebounds and two blocks. Fordham also got 11 points and four assists from Antrell Charlton. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
